titlestmt.titleproper: Guide to the Dwight Hall, Yale University, Records
titlestmt.author: compiled by Daniel Hartwig and staff of Manuscripts and Archives

publicationstmt.publisher: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on Thursday April 18, 2019 at 07:25

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The records consist of correspondence, minutes of meetings, financial records, membership lists, program records, committee records, scrapbooks, subject files, conference records, publications and printed material, and related materials concerning the activities of Dwight Hall at Yale.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 39-B (YRG 39-B), Records documenting specific religious denominations or groups.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: The records were transferred from Dwight Hall, 1988, 1994-1995, and 2018.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Access to the records is partially restricted. See Collection Contents for details.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Dwight Hall, Yale University, Records (RU 47). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The records are arranged by accession.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: Dwight Hall, a religious and service organization at Yale University, was originally founded as the Young Men's Christian Association at Yale in 1881.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The records consist of correspondence, minutes of meetings, financial records, membership lists, program records, committee records, scrapbooks, subject files, conference records, publications and printed material, and related materials concerning the activities of Dwight Hall at Yale.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: The materials are open for research.
